T4 - events occurring in the future, around 2010+ We witness the events that led to John meeting Kyle, surviving the ordeal and reach the time machine to send Kyle back to close the circle of events on all terminator movies.  T5 - alternate timeline generated by the T-X passing the experience and info of future SKYNET to 2k's SKYNET and acquiring new experience correcting itself. text: So I'm thinking the pitch for this went like...  "The Terminator movies after 2 were bad, fans didn't like the dumb convoluted plots, bad cgi, whiny John O' Connor, the addition of women who couldn't fill Linda Hamilton's combat boots and Arnie being a bit old on the intimidating death machine scale. So let's restart the series with another convoluted plot, more bad cgi, remove John altogether and put in two more woke women while propping up an even older Arnie and Linda." X.X  Honestly the nostalgia factor of Arnie and Linda is the only thing keeping the series alive which as much as I like those characters isn't a good thing. What they should do is restart the series completely with a new terminator, a simple plot (stress SIMPLE) like the original that keeps the action going with none of convolution. Then have Arnie and Linda in supporting (but respectable) camo roles for the fanservice but not their original characters. Don't kill them stupidly like Star Wars did. They should also trash the whole lithe nano-terminator bit and go back to the unstoppable rock'em sock'em robots we know and love. Yes T2's liquid terminator was a great villain but you get into a one up battle if you advance the tech too quickly.

text: What really made Terminator 2 was the the Practical effects along with the updated computer technology of the time. Stan Winston was great. I feel like this new Terminator is just a rehash of the John Connor in Terminator Genisys. I was really looking forward to something that was new from James Cameron like a different approach to his Terminator story. Like when we saw the T-1000 in Terminator 2 we were really Blown Away. But I can't criticize the movie yet because I haven't seen it I just hope it's a different approach.  in Terminator 2 just to see Arnold as a Defender rather than a killer was something that was a new approach. Then to see a new killer other than the Terminator we seen as Arnold I think that is what really made Terminator 2 great.  I think there's just an over-reliance on computer technology rather than practical effects. For example that scene when Arnold went in and was shooting around the cops and cops started shooting back at him there was an Arnold Schwarzenegger mannequin type they rolled up slowly making it look like he was getting hit by bullets. Then that scene when the T-1000 was barricaded by the bars and walked right through them that was a good use of computer technology. Now it just seems that there is just an overuse.  off topic but that's why I appreciate what Jason Reitman is going to do in the new Ghostbusters movie where he's going to use practical effects rather than computer technology like the all-female Ghostbusters. My opinion though...

text: This looks stupid as all hell. The writers are just banking on "girl power". Terminator 1984 would have been a good movie no matter who the hero was, and they used the lens of motherhood to add a twist to the story. This movie? The girl they're saving is 4th billed. She only exists as an excuse to make this movie.   The whole point of the Terminators is that they're unstoppable. Arnold didn't need to run, because like the big rig he just couldn't be stopped. The reason the liquid metal Terminator was so scary in Terminator 2 is that he was doing things you didn't expect a Terminator to do. Now we all know the Terminators are doing to do stupid CGI moves. It's not surprising. The thing that would actually scare people is if the new Terminator didn't actually have any special abilities at all. Imagine if 1984 just got upgraded so he was smarter, and could tap into people's cell phones and stuff. He would always be able to find you. And he would never stop. THAT is what Terminator is about.   ...but it's a lot easier to pay a special effects studio to come up with stupid fights.

text: Doesn't anyone want to discuss the Skynet new prototype terminator seen on this trailer?  It's a two-in-one terminator that can split into a T-900 exoskeletal model (the next generation T-800) and a T-1000 liquid metal polymer model, both of which can operate independently of each other.  Whoever the screenwriter is, I salute his/her fertile imagination.  I wished I had thought of that concept.  This is very, very bad news for the movie's good guys.  They're basically outnumbered every time they face this prototype terminator which splits into two different terminators.  It was difficult fighting one Skynet prototype terminator at a time, now two at a time when it splits.  By the way,  the 2010 Sarah Chronicles showed an excellent depiction of the early T-600/700 terminators, which utilized artificial materials for flesh and skin and didn't look realistic.  The early T-600 model did not have the natural movements of the T-800 and shambled about like a Frankenstein.  You could hear its primitive servo motors whirring and whining.  But the T-600 wasn't lacking in superhuman strength and was apparently just as capable of defeating and capturing humans.  Too bad more was not shown of the early but failed T-600 series, just for entertainment's sake.

text: Stop. Just... Stop. Please.  Look, the first two films were great becaues they started from somethign resembling a plausible sceince fiction premise. Thye aimed to make you believe in the world.  Since Terminator 3 it's been ever increasing insanity. Now you got CGI shit just flying all over the place constantly. There's no character. no drama. no real belief in the story.  The Terminator was about two people finding love in the darkest of times. Terminator 2 was about the vale of human life and that we are all important, somewhere, at some time.   These new films don't have a purpose. They don't have a focus. They don't understand what  a TERMINATOR is or why it even came to be. They don't understand that Skynet shouldn't have a face. It's not a villain because it's the bad guy. It's a villain to us because it is a cold calculating machine intelligence that has no humanity. terminators exist to infiltrate and kill us from within. They're an opportunity to try and understand more about what it is to be human. If our society is so deayed that a walking killing machine can patrol though a crowd of us unnoticed, what does that say about us? How far away from our machines are we really?   Since Terminator 3, the films have given up their brain.  Also, I know.. TL;DR, but... Having Arnold make a glorified cameo, and having J.C. put his name on this is NO guarantee. Arnie has not made smart choices with the Terminator franchise up to this point. He should have put his foot down on T3 and forced them to make the script better. He had the pull. James Cameron simply can't be trusted anymore. He gave major kudos to Genisys, which was awful. Truly awful.

text: Looking at the comments that complain about how pathetic the new villain Terminator looks has made me realize that people seem to have forgotten about the entire point of the Terminator itself. The idea is that the Terminator sent back in time is supposed to be able to blend in at first glance and be unassuming before going apeshit for the kill, and the otherwise unintimidating dude they picked for the role fits that description almost perfectly. And as for the complaints about the film looking "SJW" because it prominently features women and a Hispanic dude, grow the fuck up! Why does the gender/ethnicity of the cast offend you so much that you'll let it completely ruin a trailer for you? Not every film that features female leads is Ghostbusters 2016, I mean has everyone forgotten that the original Terminator itself had a female lead in it? And who says the Terminator can't take the form of an ethnic person, because I sure as fuck don't remember Kyle Reese telling Sarah Connor "The Terminator can look exactly like a human, unless the human form is anything but a Caucasian person."     Now as for the trailer itself, the film is clearly not going to top the original Terminator film or T2, but I honestly don't expect it to. In fact, in a perfect world Hollywood would have simply let the franchise conclude with T2. At the very least the trailer doesn't seem to give away spoilers and immediately signal alarm bells like a certain other Terminator trailer did (*cough* *cough* GENISYS*), the action and set pieces look appealing enough, and I'll admit I got excited when I saw Sarah Connor. I'm not going to say it's going to be a masterpiece, hell for all I know this could end up being the worst movie of 2019, but at the very least it doesn't look terrible. And for a franchise that has films like Terminator 3 and Genisys under its belt, I'll take not terrible.

text: "How do we win?"  You don't.  The whole set up of the Terminator franchise is an impossible win, regardless what they try to sell you movie and book wise.  I am not familiar with the very first Hunter Killers, but anything 800 and up should basically be unstoppable without some freakishly high tech weaponry or incredible and highly trained military odds.  The human race was basically all, but exterminated by the nuclear holocaust.  Those remaining pockets of humanity than had to deal with unstoppable machines with just ordinary weaponry, which had to of been quite few to begin with.  Salvaging simply does not cut it.  Reprogramming a few Ts should not put a dent in the odds.  It takes probably more than 100 bullets to stop a T and that is a low count anyway.  They can see you during the day and night no problem.  They never need to rest or eat.  Their weapons cut through any modern human body armor.  Simply put, no matter what John Connor or anyone else does the machines are unstoppable and that is what makes them so awesome.  If they were push overs it be pointless to watch.  Why Skynet keeps going back in time I have no idea.  Just destroy the humans in the present (our future).

text: Remember when it was just two people being chased around a factory by a lurching 'sometimes stop motion sometimes not' metal terror? This demonstrates the importance and power of limitation in art and how it can sometimes improve a product.   The problem is not the advance in technology (T2 demonstrated that very well too) but the way it's applied and increasingly over-relied upon to distract from a lack of meaningful story, with good acting, character development and scenes that draw you into the reality that's been created.  Subtlety is being eroded in favour of an ever-increasing need for excess. Sensory excitement is temporary, no matter how pleasurable, but the imparting of an impactful meaning in a story can stay with you forever. It doesn't even have to be profound, it just has to work.  PS: Having said all that, I will watch this movie before condemning completely, I'm not stuck in nostalgia, there are some great movies that have come out recently, but the landscape of cinema changed a long time ago and I'm not sure it's in a good direction.

text: This does not look good. There is nothing wrong with a strong female character. We've had hundreds if not thousands of them in film and they've never received anything but love from 'the man' or 'the white man'. The problem with SJW/Millennial/Liberal/Diversity/Victim writing is....it is bad writing. 'Get woke. Go Broke.' Is a saying for a reason. Traditional story telling and escapism has very clear tropes, themes, and arcs. SJWs want to 'subvert your expectation' which is code word for shoving SJW ideals down your throat. All white men are either evil or incompetent and thus disposable. There will never be a 'boy meets girl' situation, because all milliennials come from broken homes and have no social skills themselves, and can not make any long term relationship work, so they buck tradition and destroy all relationships within any story they tell, especially traditional hetero relationships. Diversity(more female and brown face on the screen for no reason please) and girl power is the key! All girls are super independent and don't need no man! Not for love. Not for help. Not for anything. Women are super strong and capable, make all the decisions and will save the day....translation: butch looking asexual woman pretending to be a man, which is such a turn off, physically, mentally, and unbelievable from a storytelling standpoint. SJW women are not proud to be women. They are confused about their sexuality and resent any feminine/sexy woman who is able to project sexual power. SJW men are more feminine and womanly in mentality and appearance than the women are. They are confused messes, and thus so is their writing. And they are all miserable. That is why their story telling is miserable. That is why you go to see their movies and walk out of the theater feeling miserable yourself and like you just got robbed of your 10 bucks and your 2 hours of life. Stories, books, music, movies are all a way for us to experience 'escapism'. SJW writing subverts and DESTROYS ESCAPISM. Why you feel so terrible when you leave the theater after seeing a movie like this is because it is not escapism...it is propaganda and identity politics. It looks terrible. It feels terrible. The stories are never good. I feel sorry for Arnold being involved in this; now there was a real man once upon a time. If he was picking the back of a truck up as the terminator you could believe it because you might see him in real life doing the same thing. Now we see this skinny blonde girl with her butch hair cut doing all these feats of strength...when we know that person in real life couldn't pick up a heavy sack of potatoes. It's ridiculous. Stop pretending to be a man. Men are men for a reason, and women are women for a reason. Be proud of what you are and write stories that reflect those strengths. They got this right 40 years ago with movies like Alien and Terminator and even Star Wars with Carrie Fisher as Princess Leia. And now here we are in 2019 having to sit through this ridiculous age of entertainment while all the SJWs get their participation badges in action movies. You can't even suspend your disbelief over a women pretending to be a man on screen doing things that a man could actually do in real life, but not her. It's silly. Entertainment is dying. There are too many movies I've spent my money on in the last 10 years where I walked out of the theater to shake my head and think 'WTF did I just watch??' Get woke. GO BROKE.

(NON CGI aside from body damage) Dreadful claustrophobic car chases.  Trickery and sinister actions.  Horror movie levels of anticipation and fear.  The feeling you are being followed.  Hopelessness and terror.    Now the new movies take on suspense is just -"Lets make everything explode non stop and turn it into a washed up video game atmosphere where no action has any meaning, rinse and repeat it over and over"   Its lost all of its horror/sci-fi elements... in turn, killing the franchise. Terminator Salvation was the last turning point, barely managing to keep the desperate feeling. But this new one, just no. It's basically Michael Bay meets Terminator mash up. I'll pass on this one...

text: My version of the next terminator movie- the future wars are raging on. Jon Conner is fighting back with all of his force but skynet is crippling his optimism. A young freedom fighter named rose who grew up after the war, has discovered who her mother was. She unfortunately was killed in the explosions and in a fit of rage, rose uses the teleportation device to travel back to the year 2019 in an effort to find her and bring her back to the future. Jon discovers this and sends an aging model 101 terminator who was scheduled for permanent deactivation the next day due to John finding the model outdated and has lost respect for the 101 due to him deactivating for nothing in 1995.Arnold is old but is determined to follow orders and track rose down and bring her back before she causes a time paradox. But roses mother doesn’t want to be found. She used to work in skynet in the 90s and is ashamed of what she was but is unaware of the future to come. Skynet in the future sends a new terminator to stop rose before she can make contact with her mother in hopes of keeping the mother alive and persuade her to work again with skynet and develop technology at a faster rate in the year 2019, thus causing skynet to win the war. Judgement day will always happen. But it is continuously postponed due to one woman. Sarah Connor. Who has spent her entire life keeping the war at bay. But little does she know that the war cannot be stopped. She finds rose in the year 2019 and agrees to help her find her mother. Rose discovers her mom and discovers that her name is lily. Arnold manages to find them and he speaks with rose in private. Sarah is shocked at Arnold’s appearance. Eventually a terminator strikes at the group, attempting to capture Lily and make her work yet again at skynet in an effort to develop new advanced technology before the official war begins in 2021. Disguised as a normal human, the terminator uses lily as a slave and watches her close as she works. It is now up to Arnold, rose and Sarah to save her before the future of humanity is lost. Young John is an author in New York City unaware of the horror that his mother is once again experiencing. Arnold and the terminator battle as lily returns to rose. Lily tells rose that she wishes she could spend more time with her and that she gave her up as a baby because she felt unfit to raise a child due to her work at cyberdine in 1995. She apologizes. But the terminator isn’t the defeated. It aims at rose but lily gets in the way and is killed. Arnold kills the the terminator and informs rose that lily was always going to die and that there’s no changing that. Arnold is badly injured but is still in one piece. Arnold shakes hands with Sarah, knowing that she will die of radiation poisoning while helping a family during the start of the war in 2021. Rose and Arnold decide to return back home to the future of 2047. Arnold is deemed as a hero and is rebuilt. John finally forgives the terminator for leaving him in 1995 and allows him to be a member of the resistance. Then the terminator franchise ends with a message. That judgement day can never be stopped. It could be postponed for years but in 2021, nothing can stop it

text: This may be what JAMES CAMERON  originally had in mind with two terminators for the T1 movie. When writing the draft for the original movie initially it involved two Terminators being sent to the past. The first was similar to the Terminator in the 1st film, while the second was made of liquid metal and could not be destroyed with conventional weaponry. Because special effects in the early 80's could not create liquid metal the way he wanted he saved it for a second movie T2 in the early 90's. But i think T6 might of been the original concept? 2 terminators in one? It looks good, I hope the writing is much better then the action i've seen so far in this trailer.                       sourced: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Terminator

text: My simple plot for Terminator Dark fate:  It's the middle of the war between humans and machines. Arnold is just a human ex-marine that is living his end of days through the rubble but Terminators are on to him to extract his DNA and create the T-800. (We don't take T3 in consideration) He is old, he is tired, and he tries to hide. He is devastated once he learns the story that some Terminators from the past looked like him, from his new retired cop friend played by an old Robert Patrick. It's just a matter of time 'till a terminator finds them. Once they are found they try to fight off a bulky non-skinned Terminator guerilla war style. They know that they cannot win. After a while they both get caught and get cloned. Patrick dies honorable death in order to free up Arnold. At the end, Arnold finds the resistance leader, John Connor (Edward Furlong) they form a bond because John feels he already knows Arnie and looks to him as an old father figure. They agree to send a T2 into the past to make sure a young John is protected. As a redemptive way Arnold proposes that they create the type of Terminator that can learn and understand human emotions and that could teach John to be a man and a leader, Arnold sacrifices himself like a hero and uploads a part of his consciousness onto the T-800 chip that is only activated when needed (by Sarah in the T2). This death scene should play as an homage to the death of the T-800 in T2.  When the aparatus that sucks the life out of him turnes on with the human Arnie in the main seat, the Terminator theme starts in the background. In order to show the humanity in this installment, the Terminator soundtrack should all be played by an orchestra.  This could be a blockbuster and movie that could evoke real emotions that could remain a classic for all time, if done correctly.

text: Years ago, after watching the first Matrix, I had this crazy Idea.  (Terminatrix)    The year is 2050. This war between man and machines has been endless.  Machines were smart, they never stopped learning, growing becoming more than, just a machine.   Terminators evolved countless times becoming harder and harder to detect.  Now cyborgs, more human than machine, the hardest of them all to detect.   Human brains are being reprogrammed.  Electronic chips connected into every nerve of the human body giving these new Terminators super human strength, all pain sensors, disabled, replaced with injury only sensors. All these years we had hope because of my grandfather Kyle Reese, it was all an illusion.   Like the machine’s humans watched and learned.   We learned from the very first appearance of the T101, while they evolved, they needed electricity.   We fought back, it was carnage, our species is down to a few hundred thousand across the planet. We won a few battles, they replenished their ranks, we could not. In our final attacks, we destroyed all their damn power sources. We now know this is their only weakness.   If you are reading this, it means there are survivors.  Some of us had to do the unthinkable to save our species from extermination, kamikaze attacks.  It became the only way; all our defenses were detected before they ever left the ground. Humans were the only source for carrying out and detonating explosives. So many good men and women lost, even children are being picked to carry out these attacks. Fuck these machines! Hope you all, fucking die!   Russia being the only country left with hidden undisclosed bunkers with Nukes.  Along with their remaining scientist and ours, we have been able to attach radioactive batteries from fallen Terminators, creating what we call, the earth destroyer bomb.   This would, will cause a complete black out on earth, meaning no sun, no solar power, no electricity, all computer chips fried, also meaning, no food can be grown. We all agreed it could be the destruction of earth itself, but what choice do we have? It is either be destroyed by machines, or destroy ourselves to destroy these SOB’s. As I sit here, I can only think about humanity and hope, we are losing this war, this is our last hope.     May my sacrifice end this for good, the date is August 15th 2050, this is Lieutenant Kayla Reese.     Kayla pushes the button detonating the earth destroyer sacrificing herself.
